SEES Typhoid run_mod jags output

Source: R/nepal_sees_jags_output.R
nepal_sees_jags_output.Rd

A run_mod() output using the nepal_sees example data set as input and stratifying by column "bldculres", which is the diagnosis type (typhoid or paratyphoid). Keeping only IDs "newperson", "sees_npl_1", "sees_npl_2".

Usage

nepal_sees_jags_output

Format

nepal_sees_jags_output

A list consisting of the following named elements:

curve_params

A data.frame titled curve_params that contains the posterior predictive distribution of the person-specific parameters for a "new person" with no observed data (Subject = "newperson") and posterior distributions of the person-specific parameters for two arbitrarily-chosen subjects ("sees_npl_1" and "sees_npl_2")

attributes

A list of attributes that summarize the jags inputs

Source

reference study: https://doi.org/10.1016/S2666-5247(22)00114-8
